  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc6\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 181 \u0b93\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "India scored 181 runs against Pakistan",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Batting first in the ongoing Asia Cup Super 4 match against Pakistan in Dubai, United Arab Emirates, India scored 181 runs for the loss of 7 wickets in 20 overs.",
        "Pakistan captain Babar Azam, who won the toss of the match, announced that his team will field first.",
        "India got off to a blistering start with skipper Rohit Sharma and Lokesh Rahul before falling to Haris Raf and Shadab Khan in subsequent overs with Sharma on 28 (16) and Rahul on 28 (20).",
        "Suryakumar Yadav fell to Mohammad Nawaz after the allotted time and Rishabh Pant and Hardik Pandya fell to Shadab Khan and Mohammad Hasnain in successive overs. Deepak Hooda also fell for Naseem Shah after the appointed time.",
        "In this situation, India scored 181 runs for the loss of 7 wickets in 20 overs with 60 (44) runs from Virat Kohli who was run out in the last over."
      ],
